Bug 2029007 - Preserve <pre> formatting when quoting a selection from an HTML message. r=mkmelin

Previously, replying with a partial selection from an email only preserved <pre> formatting
if the original message was a plain-text email wrapped by Thunderbird (using the
moz-text-plain class). This caused native HTML emails with <pre> tags to lose their
formatting, collapsing newlines into spaces when partially quoted.

This patch updates nsMsgComposeService::OpenComposeWindow to traverse the DOM tree upwards
from the selection's focus node, checking if the selection resides inside any <pre> block.
It ensures the quoted text is wrapped in <pre class="moz-quote-pre"> for both plain-text
emails and native HTML preformatted blocks.

Also adds a new Mochitest (test_html_pre) to browser_replySelection.js to prevent future
regressions.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292233

diff --git a/mailnews/compose/src/nsMsgComposeService.cpp b/mailnews/compose/src/nsMsgComposeService.cpp
--- a/mailnews/compose/src/nsMsgComposeService.cpp
+++ b/mailnews/compose/src/nsMsgComposeService.cpp
@@ -366,18 +366,31 @@ nsMsgComposeService::OpenComposeWindow(
            type == nsIMsgCompType::ReplyToList)) {
         nsCOMPtr<nsINode> node = selection->GetFocusNode();
         nsAutoCString selHTML;
         if (node && NS_SUCCEEDED(GetOrigWindowSelection(selection, selHTML))) {
+          // Traverse the DOM tree upwards to check if the selection is
+          // inside a <pre> tag.
+          bool isInsidePre = false;
+          for (nsCOMPtr<nsINode> parentNode = node; parentNode;
+               parentNode = parentNode->GetParentNode()) {
+            if (parentNode->LocalName().EqualsLiteral("pre")) {
+              isInsidePre = true;
+              break;
+            }
+          }
+          // Wrap in <pre> if it's an actual HTML <pre> block or a plain-text
+          // email.
           IgnoredErrorResult er;
-          if ((node->LocalName().IsEmpty() ||
-               node->LocalName().EqualsLiteral("pre")) &&
-              node->OwnerDoc()->QuerySelector(
-                  "body > div:first-of-type.moz-text-plain"_ns, er)) {
-            // Treat the quote as <pre> for selections in moz-text-plain bodies.
-            // If focusNode.localName isn't empty, we had e.g. body selected
-            // and should not add <pre>.
+          if (isInsidePre ||
+              ((node->LocalName().IsEmpty() ||
+                node->LocalName().EqualsLiteral("pre")) &&
+               node->OwnerDoc()->QuerySelector(
+                   "body > div:first-of-type.moz-text-plain"_ns, er))) {
+            // Treat the quote as <pre> for selections in actual <pre> tags or
+            // moz-text-plain bodies. If focusNode.localName isn't empty, we
+            // had e.g. body selected and should not add <pre>.
             pMsgComposeParams->SetHtmlToQuote(
-                "<pre class=\"moz-quote-pre\" wrap=\"\">"_ns + selHTML +
+                R"(<pre class="moz-quote-pre" wrap="">)"_ns + selHTML +
                 "</pre>"_ns);
           } else {
             pMsgComposeParams->SetHtmlToQuote(selHTML);
           }
